type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

By default, typing in the palette filters the //current stage's// visible rows by substring match against each row's `name` and `hint` slots. Three pill strips widen this:

! Reach (where) — mutually exclusive

|!Pill |!Leader |!Walks |
|🔍 Here |`d` |Every reachable drill below the current stage |
|🌐 Everywhere |`g` |Every reachable drill from the active view's root |

Picking a Reach result replays the drill path so the cascade arrives at the row's natural parent.

! Meta (cascade-item author meta) — accumulating

Pills tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-meta`. Matcher reads `item[ca-meta-key]`.

|!Pill |!Reads |
|🏷 Name |Row's display name (default if no pills) |
|💡 Hint |Row's subtitle (default if no pills) |

! Field (literal tiddler fields) — accumulating

Pills tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-field`. Matcher reads `wiki.getTiddler(item.title).fields[ca-tiddler-field]`. Synthetic rows skip silently.

|!Pill |!Reads |
|📄 Text |Backing tiddler's `text` field — body |

! Push everything

Leader `a` — pushes both Meta pills (Name, Hint) plus the Text Field pill. Equivalent to "match anywhere".

Active pills in each strip //union//; the matcher reads the combined slot set.

! Multi-match visualisation

A row that matches in multiple slots gets:

* ''Inline highlight'' on its name / hint (whichever matched).
* ''One snippet line per non-displayed match'' — beneath the row, prefixed by the matched pill's chip + context window around the hit.

! Picking a deep result — three gestures

When Reach is active, results carry a drill path. Three keys distinguish what happens after the path replays:

|!Gesture |!Effect |
|`↵` Enter |Replay path + fire (drill into drills, execute leaves) |
|`→` Right |Replay path + drill only (no-op on plain leaves) |
|`Space` |''Pin only'' — replay path, select row, do NOT fire. Safe for destructive matches. |

''→'' Full deep-search docs: <$link to="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/doc/deep-search">doc/deep-search</$link>
